This program will execute a function call and write some information to a log file.
An example is:

auto_logger.py -set ~/mylog.txt
auto_logger.py -c "echo \"ECHO, ECHo, ECho, Echo, echo, ech., ec.., ec.., e..., ...\"" -note "A pretend echo call"

After running, look at the log.

cat ~/mylog.txt

Wed Oct 12 12:40:56 PDT 2016
$ pwd
/home/derstudent
# A pretend echo call
echo "ECHO, ECHo, ECho, Echo, echo, ech., ec.., ec.., e..., ..."

